{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-b687c5c605a2",
  "content": "## Strategy Implementations\n\n### AstChunker (corvia-adapter-git)\n\n**Formats:** .rs, .py, .js, .jsx, .ts, .tsx\n\n- `chunk()`: Tree-sitter AST parse, extract top-level constructs. Filters 1-liners.\n- `split_oversized()`: Recurse into child AST nodes. 500-line `impl` splits into methods. Huge functions split at inner block boundaries. Fallback: line-based split.\n- `merge_small()`: Scope-aware sibling merge. Two one-liners in the same `impl` block merge. Cross-scope chunks don't. Uses `merge_group` metadata hint.\n- `overlap_context()`: Prepend parent signature (e.g., `impl AuthService {` for a method chunk).\n\n\n### MarkdownChunker (corvia-kernel)\n\n**Formats:** .md\n\n- `chunk()`: Split at heading boundaries (`#`, `##`, `###`). Each section = heading + body.\n- `split_oversized()`: Recursive heading descent → paragraph splitting (`\\n\\n`) → sentence-level.\n- `merge_small()`: Merge adjacent sections at same heading level under same parent.\n- `overlap_context()`: Carry heading hierarchy (e.g., `## Auth\\n### JWT\\n`).\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.3-embedding-chunking-design.md",
